This is an action RPG boss battle. Avoid the enemy's attacks
and attack with the A key. While holding the D key, you can
move with your direction fixed.

If either your stamina or health reaches 0 from the enemy's
attacks, you will be defeated. Generally, ranged attacks
will decrease your health, and contact will decrease your
stamina.

When you come into contact with the enemy, you'll be held
and continue to take damage until you succeed at the timing
bar. Let me show you the timing bar.

Stopping on yellow is a success, stopping on red is a
critical. If you stop on yellow, you'll take damage and be
released, while stopping on red will halve the damage and
release you.

Furthermore, taking damage to your stamina from the enemy
will put you in a \C[14]state of arousal\C[0], which reduces
the number of slashes during your attacks. A heart mark ♡
will appear on your status while in this state.

Arousal can be dispelled by walking around for a certain
amount of time. It can also be dispelled by achieving a
critical to shake off the enemy. If possible, aim to stop on
red.

Learn the enemy's attack patterns. The enemy's attacks have
patterns. Focus on dodging first to memorize them.

Make use of the D key's direction lock. Locking your
direction makes it easier to attack and dodge. Attacking
while retreating can make the battle easier.

Use healing items and skills. There are no usage limits for
healing items and skills (like deep breathing). You can heal
and push through aggressively if needed.

Use the Action Ease option. Turning on Action Ease from the
options will significantly lower the difficulty level. There
are no downsides to this.
